Package: bfbtools
Type: Package
Title: Linear-Time Breakage-Fusion-Bridge Count-Vector Algorithms
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Giovanni", "Santacatterina", email = "you@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides linear-time algorithms for deciding whether a
    chromosomal segment copy-number count-vector is consistent with the
    breakage-fusion-bridge (BFB) mechanism, and for finding the closest
    BFB-admitting count-vector to a noisy observed one under a
    probabilistic error model. Ported from the reference Java
    implementation of Zakov, Kinsella & Bafna (2013, "An algorithmic
    approach for breakage-fusion-bridge detection in tumor genomes",
    PNAS 110(14):5546-5551), building on Kinsella & Bafna (2012,
    "Combinatorics of the Breakage-Fusion-Bridge Mechanism", J. Comput.
    Biol. 19(6):662-678). Part of the bfbtools/bfbgill/bridges family:
    this package is the sim-agnostic detection library (no dependency
    on any particular simulator); bfbgill provides Gillespie-based BFB
    simulation; bridges provides fitting, plotting, and batch detection
    glue code on top of both.
